14:43.534 --> 14:45.058
-Oh...
-NANDOR: Okay.

14:45.101 --> 14:47.277
-The floor is yours.
-I'm a little bit concerned

14:47.321 --> 14:48.452
about Topher.

14:48.496 --> 14:50.280
I think there might be
something

14:50.324 --> 14:52.282
-really wrong with him.

14:52.326 --> 14:55.024
-Topher! Aah!

14:55.068 --> 14:58.288
-He waits under my bed  and tries to bite me, for one. -NANDOR: Yes.

14:58.332 --> 15:00.029
He eats live birds and insects.

15:00.073 --> 15:02.162
I think, I think
he might be a zombie.

15:04.425 --> 15:06.427
That, my boy,
sounds like slander.

15:06.470 --> 15:09.169
Nandor, what are you going to doabout the state of the muck

15:09.212 --> 15:10.474
-pouring out of his mouth?
-Guillermo,

15:10.518 --> 15:12.302
do you have any proof
of this wild accusation?

15:12.346 --> 15:14.348
-Aah!

15:17.786 --> 15:18.830
Well, do you?

15:18.874 --> 15:20.571
He's not well!

15:20.615 --> 15:22.312
-He's freaking out.
-Yes!

15:22.356 --> 15:24.314
He's gonna eat me!
Dios mío!

15:24.358 --> 15:25.707
LASZLO:
Well, now he's
speaking in tongues.

15:25.750 --> 15:27.274
That is awful of you
to call Topher

15:27.317 --> 15:28.405
those things you just did.

15:31.147 --> 15:33.193
Exactly.

15:33.236 --> 15:36.196
Guillermo, have you
been getting enough sleep?

15:36.239 --> 15:37.980
: No. No,
I am not getting any sleep!

15:38.024 --> 15:40.287
I haven't slept
in the last two weeks,

15:40.330 --> 15:43.203
because I have to keep one eye
open to protect you guys!

15:43.246 --> 15:45.553
-Protect us from what?

15:49.339 --> 15:50.732
Nothing.

15:50.775 --> 15:52.560
I just wish you guys knew
how hard I work for you,

15:52.603 --> 15:55.215
and you don't, so that's okay,
never mind, forget it.

15:55.258 --> 15:57.304
Did you see that?

15:57.347 --> 15:59.654
-He was eating
his own dry poops.

16:05.312 --> 16:07.227
The vampire assassins
usually come at night,

16:07.270 --> 16:08.750
so I have to constantly survey
the perimeter.

16:28.291 --> 16:30.598
Topher!

16:30.641 --> 16:33.166
Topher? No, no, no, no, no, no!

16:33.209 --> 16:34.950
I don't wanna die, I don't
wanna die, I don't wanna...

16:40.651 --> 16:42.305
Sorry. Sorry.

16:42.349 --> 16:44.177
Why...?

16:44.220 --> 16:47.876
Sorry, buddy,but you were trying to kill me.

16:49.399 --> 16:51.358
High five.

16:51.401 --> 16:53.229
I don't know, bud.

16:53.273 --> 16:55.666
-Come on!
-Okay. All right.

16:55.710 --> 16:57.451
-Aw, shit.

16:57.494 --> 16:59.366
-Why?!
-Sorry, Toph.

16:59.409 --> 17:01.281
See, that's why
I didn't want to do that.

17:01.324 --> 17:03.413
-Toph.

17:03.457 --> 17:05.633
No, buddy, I don't think it's
gonna go back on there, bud.

17:05.676 --> 17:08.331
High five!

17:08.375 --> 17:09.724
No, I'm not gonna
high-five you anymore.

17:09.767 --> 17:10.855
High five!

17:10.899 --> 17:12.814
Ow, Toph! That really hurt!

17:12.857 --> 17:14.598
-High five!
-Stop it, you...

17:14.642 --> 17:16.470
You're being really rude
right now!

17:16.513 --> 17:18.124
-Stop it! Stop it!

17:19.429 --> 17:21.388
Stop it, Topher.
Stop it, Topher!

17:21.431 --> 17:24.086
-Stop it, Topher!

17:24.130 --> 17:25.914
Aw, fuck no!

17:25.957 --> 17:28.438
No one bites Guillermo!

17:31.311 --> 17:33.313
It was an accident.

17:35.402 --> 17:37.708
All right, dudes,
I'm headed out.

17:37.752 --> 17:40.450
Going up to Albany to catch
a community theater production

17:40.494 --> 17:41.886
of Pippin.

17:44.889 --> 17:48.328
What's going on with,
uh, Toph-Dawg?

17:48.371 --> 17:50.330
I think he's a zombie.

17:50.373 --> 17:51.635
Yeah, could be.

17:51.679 --> 17:53.420
-See you guys later.

17:53.463 --> 17:55.683
You goofballs.

18:08.435 --> 18:09.523
GUILLERMO:
No!

18:09.566 --> 18:12.308
Why won't you die?!

18:15.398 --> 18:17.139
Stop it! Stop it!

18:17.183 --> 18:18.227
Ow!

18:19.968 --> 18:22.405
Jesus fucking...!

18:22.449 --> 18:25.060
Topher!

18:30.370 --> 18:32.894
Guillermo!

18:34.374 --> 18:36.289
GUILLERMO:
Master...

18:36.332 --> 18:38.204
you saved me.

18:38.247 --> 18:39.683
Thank you.

18:39.727 --> 18:42.512
Your screaming disturbed me
from my slumber.

18:42.556 --> 18:44.384
You shouldn't be putting
your head in there.

18:44.427 --> 18:45.254
It's not hygienic.

18:45.298 --> 18:46.951
If you want to wash yourself,
do it in...

18:46.995 --> 18:48.562
Will you stop that!

18:48.605 --> 18:50.781
-I've had enough of this.

18:54.568 --> 18:58.311
He was a good familiar
and a fine fellow.

18:58.354 --> 19:00.530
-But what is done is done.

19:01.966 --> 19:03.316
This fuckin' guy.

19:10.627 --> 19:13.326
He was a good familiar
and a fine fellow.

19:13.369 --> 19:14.762
But what is done is done.

19:16.459 --> 19:19.245
Are you kidding me with this
right now?

19:19.288 --> 19:22.422
Just give him a few jolts.
I'll be fine.

19:22.465 --> 19:24.511
He was a good familiar
and a fine fellow.

19:25.990 --> 19:28.428
Kind of tickles.

19:31.039 --> 19:32.519
You conned us,
you slippery bastard!

19:32.562 --> 19:34.564
Wallace,
how could you do this to us?

19:34.608 --> 19:37.001
Yeah, plus, he was crawling
on the ceiling, which is odd.

19:37.045 --> 19:39.482
-Well, he didn't do that before?-NADJA: Of course not!

19:39.526 --> 19:41.789
Well, okay, I must have used
the wrong incantation spell.

19:41.832 --> 19:44.487
But you know what?
No extra charge.

19:44.531 --> 19:46.141
-Bullshit! You made it up
as you were going along.
-No, no, no, no,

19:46.185 --> 19:48.448
that was word-for-word verbatim.

19:48.491 --> 19:50.537
No. You were bloody texting
on your phone the whole time!

19:50.580 --> 19:52.582
It was an Amber Alert.

19:52.626 --> 19:54.236
Well, I did think
it was important.

19:54.280 --> 19:57.021
He is damaged goods,
and we demand satisfaction!

19:57.065 --> 20:00.503
-Not cool, Wallace, not cool.

20:00.547 --> 20:02.331
-Fine. Let me have him.
-What, do you think

20:02.375 --> 20:04.464
I'm gonna let him go?
You must be out of your mind.

20:06.814 --> 20:08.076
Come here, boy.

20:08.119 --> 20:09.556
Come on, come on.

20:11.297 --> 20:13.777
That'll do, pig, that'll do.

20:13.821 --> 20:15.388
-Wow.
-All right,

20:15.431 --> 20:17.172
I don't normally do refunds,

20:17.216 --> 20:19.000
but I'll take him
off your hands for you.

20:19.043 --> 20:20.393
And for your trouble,

20:20.436 --> 20:23.657
each of you can grab
a license plate key chain.

20:23.700 --> 20:25.615
For free?

20:25.659 --> 20:27.182
Free. Gratis.

20:27.226 --> 20:28.749
Okay.

20:28.792 --> 20:30.533
Come on!

20:30.577 --> 20:33.493
-Oh. "Ingrid." Oh.
-NANDOR: I got...

20:33.536 --> 20:34.624
"Steve."

20:34.668 --> 20:38.585
So if you're watching, Steve...

20:38.628 --> 20:40.543
waiting for you.

20:40.587 --> 20:41.849
Ah.

20:41.892 --> 20:43.633
NADJA:
I got "Nadia," uh,

20:43.677 --> 20:46.506
which is my name,
but with a less exciting "J."

20:46.549 --> 20:48.508
Completely free.

20:48.551 --> 20:50.031
You don't have "Colin."

20:50.074 --> 20:52.512
We haven't sold any
since 1979, mate.

20:52.555 --> 20:54.514
But you have "Condom."

20:54.557 --> 20:56.603
Very, very popular.

20:56.646 --> 20:58.431
-Can I take one?
-Go for it.

20:58.474 --> 21:00.084
GUILLERMO:
So I got...

21:00.128 --> 21:01.434
"Gigi."

21:01.477 --> 21:03.914
I guess that's better
than "Gizmo."

21:07.396 --> 21:10.312
Being a familiar
isn't for everyone.

21:10.356 --> 21:14.055
You're not always thanked
or praised.

21:14.098 --> 21:17.145
But after my master
saved my life,

21:17.188 --> 21:20.104
he proved to me that...
he really does care about me

21:20.148 --> 21:22.455
and all the things I do for him.

21:22.498 --> 21:26.285
And if one day
he doesn't, well...

21:44.520 --> 21:47.567
Here you go. Down there.

21:47.610 --> 21:49.569
That be slippy there, hang on.

21:49.612 --> 21:51.919
Here you go.

21:51.962 --> 21:53.399
Topher!

21:53.442 --> 21:54.922
Yep.

21:54.965 --> 21:57.316
Just uh, copy what they do,
you'll be fine.

21:58.534 --> 21:59.796
Doze Apples!

21:59.840 --> 22:01.494
Yeah, yeah, yeah.
Very good.

22:01.537 --> 22:03.713
Be back to check on you
next year.

22:03.757 --> 22:05.976
Doze Apples.

22:06.020 --> 22:07.543
WALLACE:
Yes, yes.

